National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan recently spoke with Luigi Mattiolo, Diplomatic Advisor to the Italian Prime Minister. Sullivan expressed his desire to strengthen the bilateral partnership between the United States and Italy, while also offering condolences for the deaths of Italian Ambassador Luca Attanasio, Carabinieri Vittorio Iacovacci, and their Congolese driver Mustapha Milambo in the Democratic Republic of the Congo. Sullivan also expressed support for Italy's priorities in its G20 presidency, including addressing the COVID-19 pandemic, global health security, economic recovery, and climate change. They agreed to continue close coordination on issues of shared interest, such as Libya and the Eastern Mediterranean.